 go to the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://shadowbane.ubisoft.com/home/news.shtml">Shadowbane</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> home page and read all you can there...They have a great <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://shadowbane.ubisoft.com/home/faq/index.shtml">FAQ</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> section that answers most of your basic SB questions...<br><br>SB is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Race/Class/Discipline</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> based, which offers much more charactor customization than EQ...For example, a Healer could also have Melae or other special abilities that they can specialize in, however the more you specialize in, the less effective you will become in each skill overall...And some Disciplines require a base number of stats to even train, so some research into the Race/Class/Discipline firelds are recommended before you roll your char...<br><br><br>I will update this post as more good starting information comes available...&lt;bows&gt;...<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> &quot;...Death twitches my ear. &quot;Live,&quot; he says, &quot;I am coming...&quot;</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br> <p><center><img src=http://www.visceralstudios.com/darkgenesis/images/messageboard/ranzire_abyss_2.jpg></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub9.ezboard.com/uthonatos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thonatos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#E6E8fA>(6/4/02 7:51:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub9.ezboard.com/fdarkgenesis75448general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=232.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Basic Shadowbane Info For Those New To SB...</span><hr size=1> As an example,<br><br>  And trust me I am far from very knowledgable here on SB ( YET )...<br><br>  you can chose one of the 4 main "paths" and actually chose to either.. stay in that path.. or to expand into disciplines... for example..  a D&D term.. Multi class..  and from that new class.. you can go further..  provided you have all the requirements of that class...<br><br> It is apparent ( again I may be wrong here ) that you can get some classes that need several others are prerequisites.. to get that class.   I scanned over some classes last night at like 2 am..   it seems for instance.. To become a "dark knight" ( something that just draws my attention like someone waving a winning lotto ticket in my face ) it seems that I could get there.. by being a warrior then some sort of wizard..  actually I think i had to have both of them before a dark knight could be gained..<br><br> I could be wrong on the specifics, I probably am, but the overall idea here is not far from off <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub9.ezboard.com/umorekiltz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MorekilTZ</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#E6E8fA>(6/8/02 12:20:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub9.ezboard.com/fdarkgenesis75448general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=232.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Basic Shadowbane Info For Those New To SB...</span><hr size=1> I've been reading the SB site and I've come up with a quick layout of how you would start off in SB so you can decide now what you're going to pick:<br><br>1. Choose name and gender.<br>2. Choose your race (All races get 30 trait, talent, and ability spending points). Then choose your physical features like hair color and crap...<br>3. Choose your class type. There are four base types of fighter, mage, healer, and rogue<br>4. Decide where to put your points - IMO this is the most critical stage in creating your character because every wrong skillpoint may result in deciding on either recreating your character or going on regretting you didn't put more points into a certain ability.<br>5. Disciplines come later in the game. They are runes which have to be found and bound to your character and cannot be removed.<br><br>Go <A HREF="http://shadowbane.ubisoft.com/gameinfo/races.shtml"><br>here</A> and you can pick out your character and maybe write down what you're going to choose before even buying the game.<br><br>Hope this helps <p><center><a href="http://www.mutedfaith.com/quiz/qz4.htm" target="new"><img src="http://www.mutedfaith.com/images/life.jpg" border=0></a><br><a href="http://www.mutedfaith.com/quiz/qz4.htm" target="new">find your element</a>at <a href="http://www.mutedfaith.com" target="new">mutedfaith.com</a>.<a href="http://www.livejournal.com/users/labile"><º></a></center><center> <a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=80710 ">See my gear</a></center> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub9.ezboard.com/uranzire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ranzire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member Of The Inner Circle</span><br>  Posts: 163<br> <font color=#E6E8fA>(6/8/02 12:25:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub9.ezboard.com/fdarkgenesis75448general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=232.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Basic Shadowbane Info For Those New To SB...</sp